  "comment": "First-party plugin catalog. Embedded into the orca binary via include_str! in plugin_manager.rs AND served as the canonical remote manifest from raw.githubusercontent.com/argyle-labs/orca/main/projects/system/src/plugin_catalog.json. Adding a first-party plugin = adding one entry here and merging to main. 'status' values: 'available' = the external repo publishes per-target release assets and is installable via `plugin.install --name <name>`; 'unreleased' = the repo exists and is actively developed but publishes no release asset yet (install-by-name is refused until it cuts a release; `plugin.install --file` still sideloads a local build); 'planned' = not yet extracted into its own repo. Keep this in sync with reality \u2014 verify against the repo (does it exist? does it publish a release?), not against this field. `plugin.install --name` downloads the release asset matching the daemon's target triple ({name}-v{version}-{triple}.{so|dylib|dll}). One catalog entry == one plugin artifact: 'name'/'targetSoftware' must match the plugin's target_software() header. A single plugin may expose several tool namespaces \u2014 e.g. the 'arr' plugin bundles sonarr/radarr/prowlarr/lidarr (see its README). No hostnames or IPs \u2014 public GitHub repo URLs only.",
